doc.after: Eventually some investigators began to discover and define some of the basics of rational aircraft design Most notable of these was Leonardo da Vinci although his work remained unknown until 1797 and so had no influence on developments over the next three hundred years While his designs were at least rational they were not based on particularly good science 20
